description:
&lt;p&gt;Come and join a dynamic, motivated and innovative team. We have a busy, mixed level unit admitting emergency and elective patients from a variety of specialities. These include maxillo-facial surgery and PCi covering Kent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are excited to announce that we are expanding to 24 beds in a new purpose built Intensive Care unit within the next 6 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated person, who can be efficient and effective in the daily running of clerical duties to facilitate effective patient care. This will encompass inputting data onto a computer, tracking/tracing and collection of patients notes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.We are looking for a person who has excellent communication skills, in answering the telephone, answering the telecom system for families and MDT to enter the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a full time post with flexible working pattern covering 7 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to provide safe and effective care that exceeds the expectations of our patients and the public and we are looking for excellent staff who embraces our Trust values and care so that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· People feel cared for as individuals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· People feel safe, reassured and involved&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· People feel that we are making a difference&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· People feel teamwork, trust and respect sit at the heart of everything we do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please email the ward manager:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anna Reilly on anna.reilly@nhs.net for an informal chat or more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number01233 633331 ext 7236114&lt;/p&gt;
